{"id":"Forge-o4m","title":"Bellows drops second-wave review comments after first fix cycle completes","description":"After a reviewfix worker completes and re-requests review, NeedsFix is never cleared in the lifecycle state machine. So when the reviewer fires another EventReviewChanges (second wave), the guard !st.NeedsFix ; st.Approved evaluates to false (NeedsFix=true, Approved=false) and logs 'PR changes requested again, but already in fix cycle', dropping the second wave permanently.

Root cause: lifecycle.HandleEvent for EventReviewChanges sets NeedsFix=true but only EventCIPassed clears it. Review cycles never reset NeedsFix on completion.

Fix: After ActionFixReview completes in daemon.go, call a new lifecycle method (e.g. NotifyReviewFixCompleted) that clears NeedsFix=false so the next EventReviewChanges from the re-review gets dispatched normally.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"Robin.Edvard.Smith@fhi.no","created_at":"2026-03-06T12:02:14Z","created_by":"Robin Smith","updated_at":"2026-03-06T12:02:14Z"}

{"id":"Forge-uxg","title":"Bug: lifecycle NeedsFix flag shared between CI and review causes missed review fixes","description":"The lifecycle manager uses a single NeedsFix boolean for both CI failures and review comments. When a CI failure sets NeedsFix=true and a review change event arrives simultaneously, the review fix is skipped with 'already in fix cycle'. When CI passes and clears NeedsFix=false, the review comments are silently forgotten because bellows only triggers on the transition from 0 to >0 unresolved threads, which already happened and was missed.

Observed on PR #57 (Forge-fv5): copilot left 6 review comments, but CI failed at the same time. CI fix was dispatched and succeeded, but review comments were never addressed.

Fix: Either (a) split NeedsFix into separate CINeedsFix and ReviewNeedsFix flags, or (b) when EventCIPassed clears NeedsFix, check if HasUnresolvedThreads is still true and re-dispatch a review fix. Option (a) is cleaner — CI and review are independent fix cycles that should not block each other.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"Robin.Edvard.Smith@fhi.no","created_at":"2026-03-06T17:32:02Z","created_by":"Robin Smith","updated_at":"2026-03-06T17:32:02Z"}
